parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive unit can cause the rear wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
The failure of the rear wheel flange can cause the rear brake disc to break off while the vehicle is in motion, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Cracks in the flange around the mounting holes for the brake disc or rear wheel
rear brake disc breaks off while the vehicle is in motion.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic fuel line quick disconnect can cause fuel to leak or spray, potentially leading to a fire hazard, especially when the motorcycle is placed on the sidestand and the fuel comes into contact with the hot exhaust pipe.
symptoms: Fuel leaks or sprays from the fuel line
fuel pooling around the exhaust pipe
cracked or broken flange on the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel strip sender can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate fuel level readings, which can result in the motorcycle running out of fuel or causing other safety issues.
The failure of the fuel tank flange can cause fuel to leak, potentially leading to a fire hazard or other safety issues.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel tank
cracked or broken flange on the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracked aluminum rear wheel flange can cause the wheel to break, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Excessive movement in the rear wheel when riding through turns
cracks visible in the aluminum rear wheel flange at the wheel mounting holes.
